24:
Ngrrh... Just where are we supposed
to practice? Nimbus, you're so
selfish!
28:
Practice what? Murdering all of our
ears?
37:
It is true we haven't been able to
increase our following.
41:
Because you chase off anyone who
wants to listen. Right to their graves.
55:
Why don't you just sing normally?
Maybe something more lyrical and
less screamy?
60: Alk. What a cruel thing to say.
68: Back in Littleton, Hard Rock Magic...
73: Look, we have no set list, okay!
77: Then how are you an idol group?
82:
Waaaaah! That's exactly what that
dumb boar said!
86:
It's hard to imagine you could win a
competition without at least a few
songs under your belt.
91:
Littleton is a small, weak country. We
rarely qualified for BRASS, and when
we did, we could never secure a win.
92:
When Noenne volunteered to
compete, all we could muster was a
few dated music scores and me, a
faithful Cosmic Beast as her retainer.
96:
I have neither breath in my longs,
nor citizenship with a BRASS affiliate.
But that's how badly Noenne
needed another band mate.
102: And now Catherine's our best member!
106:
*Sigh* No one would choose this
insane situation. But we make it
work.
115:
Shall we help you prepare some
songs?
129:
Ah! I see where you're going with
this! She IS an idol after all!
147: Wait, no! It's time for a duel!
157: Try this on for sizes! RAAAAAH!
171: Cool it. We didn't come here to fight.
174: But, but I can't take another defeat!
176:
How else will Catherine, Kapipi, 
and I make Hard Rock Magic 
the best idol group in the world?!
181: Aww. What a nice dream, Noenne.
184:
I never actually wanted to be a
singer myself.
194:
But now it's different. I saw firsthand
how my music can connect hearts
and minds.
199: Hmm... Noenne, why do you sing?
203:
Never mind! I think we'll get to the
root of the problem faster if we sing
together!
206:
And, besides, performing a duet
together is a whole ton of fun!
216: Yeah. Make her into your biggest fan!
221:
Okay, let's do this! We're going to
sing our hearts out!
237: Hahaha. What kind of song was that?
240: Something new you guys cooked up?
245:
We didn't make it alone! Old Mister
Metal lent us a hand with the music.
247:
And then Dia helped make the
vocals work with the rhythm and the
melody.
251:
B-But we're just getting warmed up!
You got a problem?!
254: What? No! It was a nice song.
257:
Well, you could probably cut the
random "rah-rah" part.
